<taxonomicName id="F5C494F1BD47FFB4FEC5F8374FFCF836" authority="Kang &amp; Xue &amp; Zhang, 2019" authorityName="Kang &amp; Xue &amp; Zhang" authorityYear="2019" box="[277,472,1968,1993]" class="Insecta" family="Ptychopteridae" genus="Ptychoptera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="467" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lucida" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="00B03360BD47FFB4FEC5F8374FFCF836" bold="true" box="[277,472,1968,1993]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="467">Ptychoptera lucida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="1B838E1BBD47FFB4FE0BF8364C0EF836" box="[475,554,1969,1993]" pageId="12" pageNumber="467" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
a. Male genitalia, lateral view; b.Epandrium, dorsal view; c. Gonocoxite and gonostylus, dorsal view; d. Hypandrium, ventral view; e. Aedeagus, anterior view; f. Aedeagus, lateral view. Scale bars = 0.2 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="327BEF72BD46FFB5FF17FF1E4D9AFF28" blockId="13.[151,1437,152,1115]" pageId="13" pageNumber="468">
Abdomen (
<figureCitation id="AAFFF3F7BD46FFB5FE94FF1E4FB0FF4C" box="[324,404,153,179]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1982,2007]" captionTargetBox="[182,1371,668,1926]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[162,1426,597,1963]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 7. Ptychoptera lucida sp. nov. a. Habitus of male, lateral view, scale bar = 2.0 mm; b. Thorax, dorsal view, scale bar = 0.5 mm; c. Wing, scale bar = 1.0 mm; d. Female terminalia, lateral view, scale bar = 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3356346/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="468">Fig. 7a</figureCitation>
). Terga brownish black with posterior margins of 3rd to 5th terga pale. Sterna brownish black with posterior margins of 3rd to 7th sterna pale. Hairs on abdomen pale.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="327BEF72BD46FFB5FF17FF664F8DFD78" blockId="13.[151,1437,152,1115]" pageId="13" pageNumber="468">
Male genitalia (
<figureCitation id="AAFFF3F7BD46FFB5FEA9FF664F98FF04" box="[377,444,225,251]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="12.[151,250,1968,1993]" captionTargetBox="[249,1339,232,1907]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[165,1422,166,1948]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 8. Ptychoptera lucidasp. nov. a. Male genitalia, lateral view; b.Epandrium, dorsal view; c. Gonocoxite and gonostylus, dorsal view; d. Hypandrium, ventral view; e. Aedeagus, anterior view; f. Aedeagus, lateral view. Scale bars = 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3356348/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="468">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
) brownish black. Epandrium (
<figureCitation id="AAFFF3F7BD46FFB5FCC5FF664D43FF03" box="[789,871,225,252]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="12.[151,250,1968,1993]" captionTargetBox="[249,1339,232,1907]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[165,1422,166,1948]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 8. Ptychoptera lucidasp. nov. a. Male genitalia, lateral view; b.Epandrium, dorsal view; c. Gonocoxite and gonostylus, dorsal view; d. Hypandrium, ventral view; e. Aedeagus, anterior view; f. Aedeagus, lateral view. Scale bars = 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3356348/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="468">Fig. 8b</figureCitation>
) bilobed, lobes broad and swollen laterally with a quadrate projection on caudal area bearing dense short hairs; surstylus digitiform and broad basally with short hairs, curved inwards at middle, base with a Y-shaped lobe; proctiger bare medially, clothed with dense long hairs on posterior margin. Gonocoxite (
<figureCitation id="AAFFF3F7BD46FFB5FE22FECA4C66FE98" box="[498,578,333,359]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="12.[151,250,1968,1993]" captionTargetBox="[249,1339,232,1907]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[165,1422,166,1948]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 8. Ptychoptera lucidasp. nov. a. Male genitalia, lateral view; b.Epandrium, dorsal view; c. Gonocoxite and gonostylus, dorsal view; d. Hypandrium, ventral view; e. Aedeagus, anterior view; f. Aedeagus, lateral view. Scale bars = 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3356348/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="468">Fig. 8c</figureCitation>
) short and stout with several short hairs laterally, 1.6 times as long as wide; basal apodeme 1/3 as long as gonocoxite; paramere with two pair of projections, outer projection slender, inner projection hook-shaped. Gonostylus (
<figureCitation id="AAFFF3F7BD46FFB5FDC4FE124C46FE50" box="[532,610,405,431]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="12.[151,250,1968,1993]" captionTargetBox="[249,1339,232,1907]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[165,1422,166,1948]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 8. Ptychoptera lucidasp. nov. a. Male genitalia, lateral view; b.Epandrium, dorsal view; c. Gonocoxite and gonostylus, dorsal view; d. Hypandrium, ventral view; e. Aedeagus, anterior view; f. Aedeagus, lateral view. Scale bars = 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3356348/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="468">Fig. 8c</figureCitation>
) comprised of the following projections and lobes: a small S-shaped basal projection on inner side with short hairs; a large basal projection on dorsal side, broad at base with a small papillate projection, tapered and curved to the middle; a duckbilled lobe on middle area; an apical projection digitiform, rounded apically, with short hairs. Hypandrium (
<figureCitation id="AAFFF3F7BD46FFB5FD69FD864D2EFDE3" box="[697,778,513,540]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="12.[151,250,1968,1993]" captionTargetBox="[249,1339,232,1907]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[165,1422,166,1948]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 8. Ptychoptera lucidasp. nov. a. Male genitalia, lateral view; b.Epandrium, dorsal view; c. Gonocoxite and gonostylus, dorsal view; d. Hypandrium, ventral view; e. Aedeagus, anterior view; f. Aedeagus, lateral view. Scale bars = 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3356348/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="468">Fig. 8d</figureCitation>
) triangular, broad basally, anterior margin concaved medially; base with several lateral hairs; middle with a wide membranous region; apex with two papillate projections, dorsal papillate projection with several long hairs. Aedeagus (
<figureCitation id="AAFFF3F7BD46FFB5FC9EFDCE4DB4FD9B" box="[846,912,585,612]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="12.[151,250,1968,1993]" captionTargetBox="[249,1339,232,1907]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[165,1422,166,1948]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 8. Ptychoptera lucidasp. nov. a. Male genitalia, lateral view; b.Epandrium, dorsal view; c. Gonocoxite and gonostylus, dorsal view; d. Hypandrium, ventral view; e. Aedeagus, anterior view; f. Aedeagus, lateral view. Scale bars = 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3356348/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="468">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
eâ€“f): subapical sclerite tongue-shaped, apex of subapical sclerite round.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="327BEF72BD46FFB5FF17FD164C48FD0C" blockId="13.[151,1437,152,1115]" pageId="13" pageNumber="468">
<emphasis id="00B03360BD46FFB5FF17FD164F01FD54" bold="true" box="[199,293,657,683]" pageId="13" pageNumber="468">Female.</emphasis>
Body length 8.5â€“9.0 mm, wing length 8.5â€“9.0 mm. Similar to male. Terminalia (
<figureCitation id="AAFFF3F7BD46FFB5FB60FD164B20FD53" box="[1200,1284,657,684]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1982,2007]" captionTargetBox="[182,1371,668,1926]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[162,1426,597,1963]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 7. Ptychoptera lucida sp. nov. a. Habitus of male, lateral view, scale bar = 2.0 mm; b. Thorax, dorsal view, scale bar = 0.5 mm; c. Wing, scale bar = 1.0 mm; d. Female terminalia, lateral view, scale bar = 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3356346/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="468">Fig. 7d</figureCitation>
): 8th sternum brown and swollen ventrally at middle, 2.5 times as long as 7th sternum; cercus brown, blade-shaped, 10th tergum + cercus 1.2 times as long as 8th sternum.
</paragraph>
